02:05.692 --> 02:08.627
<i>[Thunder Rumbling]</i>

02:11.164 --> 02:14.292
I did it, Jack. I did it.

02:14.367 --> 02:17.962
And you know what?
It got me hot.

02:18.037 --> 02:20.335
No, I'm not kidding.

02:20.406 --> 02:26.038
<i>You should have seen the look</i>
<i>on Carl's face when I buried</i>
<i>that ax in his chest.</i>

02:26.112 --> 02:31.675
Ohh! Killing him was almost
better than sex.

02:31.751 --> 02:33.912
I said almost, didn't I?

02:33.987 --> 02:37.855
Ohhh! We are going
to have so much fun...

02:37.924 --> 02:41.985
spending all of his money,
aren't we, baby?

02:42.061 --> 02:45.895
Oooh! Just thinking
about it gets me all...

02:45.965 --> 02:49.696
hot and squishy.

02:49.769 --> 02:52.169
You mean right now?

02:52.238 --> 02:56.140
<i>He's in the basement</i>
<i>cooling off.</i>

03:21.034 --> 03:22.934
What took you so long?

03:23.002 --> 03:25.630
Jesus, Jack, what kind
of cologne...

03:27.340 --> 03:29.638
<i>[Gasps, Screaming]</i>

03:32.111 --> 03:34.045
Cut!

03:34.113 --> 03:36.104
Cut, cut, cut, cut, cut!

03:36.182 --> 03:39.276
<i>What the hell are you doing?</i>

03:39.352 --> 03:41.286
You call that "hack-ting"?

03:41.354 --> 03:44.482
Well, yes,
I do call it acting.

03:44.557 --> 03:49.153
Well, let me tell you something.
You're no "Gorey" Cooper.

03:49.229 --> 03:51.754
<i>You ain't even</i>
<i>a Robert "Deadford."</i>

03:51.831 --> 03:55.528
<i>Another take like that</i>
<i>and it'll be back</i>
<i>to bit parts for you.</i>

03:55.602 --> 03:58.230
And I won't say what bits
I'm talking about.

03:58.304 --> 04:01.671
<i>Huh! All right,</i>
<i>everybody. Reset!</i>

04:01.741 --> 04:03.504
Reset, guys.

04:03.576 --> 04:06.340
Director?

04:06.412 --> 04:09.779
Where the hell did
they dig this guy up?

04:09.849 --> 04:13.808
I give and I give and I...
Oh!

04:13.886 --> 04:17.652
Hello, kiddies.
So glad you could join me.

04:17.724 --> 04:22.491
Your old pal the Crypt Keeper
has gone Hollywood in a big way.

04:22.562 --> 04:24.462
Care to see what I've been
working on?

04:26.366 --> 04:30.063
So if you're ready, creeps,
fasten your drool cups...

04:30.136 --> 04:32.696
and hold on to
your vomit bags.

04:32.772 --> 04:35.468
We're going to the movies!

04:35.541 --> 04:39.841
Frights! Camera!
Action!

04:44.384 --> 04:47.319
<i>I call this one...</i>

05:01.834 --> 05:05.031
<i>#Now that the smoke's gone #</i>

05:06.472 --> 05:09.908
<i>#And the air is clear #</i>

05:12.645 --> 05:15.978
<i># Those who are right there #</i>

05:18.151 --> 05:20.915
<i># Got a cool kind of view #</i>

05:23.523 --> 05:26.924
<i># You fight and you were right #</i>

05:26.993 --> 05:30.258
<i>#But they were</i>
<i>just too strong #</i>

05:32.432 --> 05:36.926
<i># That's why I say</i>
<i>hey, man, nice shot #</i>

05:38.438 --> 05:41.032
<i># What a good shot, man #</i>

05:44.410 --> 05:48.938
<i>#Hey, baby #</i>

05:49.015 --> 05:51.540
<i>[Tires Screeching]</i>

05:51.617 --> 05:54.450
<i># That's good #</i>

05:54.520 --> 06:00.584
<i>#Hey, baby #</i>

06:00.660 --> 06:04.858
<i>[Engine Knocking]</i>

06:04.931 --> 06:07.900
<i>##[Continues]</i>

06:12.238 --> 06:14.172
<i>[Engine Dying]</i>

06:18.611 --> 06:20.841
[Tires Screeching]

06:25.685 --> 06:27.585
Come on!

06:31.190 --> 06:33.124
Son of a bitch!

06:38.030 --> 06:40.464
Come on,
you son of a bitch!

06:46.873 --> 06:49.501
Oh, shit!

06:50.843 --> 06:52.743
Damn!

07:33.553 --> 07:36.078
<i>#I wish I would've met you #</i>

07:38.958 --> 07:41.426
<i>#Now it's a little late #</i>

07:44.397 --> 07:46.831
<i># What you could've taught me #</i>

07:49.869 --> 07:52.337
<i>#I could've saved some face #</i>

07:55.208 --> 08:01.044
<i># They think that your early</i>
<i>ending was all wrong #</i>

08:05.785 --> 08:09.050
<i># Through most of the daylight #</i>

08:09.121 --> 08:13.057
<i>##[Singing Fades]</i>

08:13.125 --> 08:17.459
<i>[Thunder Rumbling]</i>

08:20.299 --> 08:22.233
[Panting]

08:28.841 --> 08:31.776
<i>[Thundering Continues]</i>

08:48.361 --> 08:50.295
What ya doin', mister?

08:50.363 --> 08:54.925
- Are you stealing
my daddy's car?
- Stealin'?

08:55.001 --> 08:59.062
No, I was testing the lock.
Seems to be working just fine.

08:59.138 --> 09:01.299
You want a quarter?

09:01.374 --> 09:05.470
How about a shiny new quarter?
You want one?

09:05.545 --> 09:08.309
Dad, there's a guy outside
stealing your car!

09:08.381 --> 09:11.316
<i>Hey, Dad, hurry up.</i>
<i>Get out here!</i>

09:16.289 --> 09:18.587
Homer, go!
He's gone.

09:26.432 --> 09:28.366
[Moaning]

09:28.434 --> 09:32.666
<i>[Thunder Rumbling]</i>
Boy, listen
to that thunder.

09:32.738 --> 09:35.571
God's doing some
serious thinking tonight.

09:35.641 --> 09:37.836
<i>[Laughing]</i>

09:37.910 --> 09:40.936
[Groaning]

09:41.013 --> 09:43.072
I'll bet he's saying,

09:43.149 --> 09:46.641
"On second thought,
maybe I should have given
it all to the monkeys."

09:46.719 --> 09:50.621
- Maybe it's not to late.
- I always hate drinking alone.
You want a taste?

09:52.358 --> 09:53.518
Sure.

09:56.262 --> 09:59.197
<i>[Thunder Rumbling]</i>

10:00.666 --> 10:02.600
To the monkeys.

10:05.738 --> 10:09.538
[Coughs]
It ain't very subtle,
but it does the trick.

10:09.609 --> 10:13.204
You wouldn't happen to know
of a place where I could
bed down, would you?

10:13.279 --> 10:15.372
Well, it just
so happens, I do.

10:15.581 --> 10:18.015
<i>[Woman On Police Radio]</i>
<i>That's two cars, Sheriff?</i>
That's right, Mavis.

10:18.084 --> 10:21.713
One of ‘em’s got Maryland
plates, and the other one's
from New Jersey.

10:21.787 --> 10:23.721
Ten-four.
Ten-four.

10:25.091 --> 10:27.025
You were right, Sheriff.

10:27.093 --> 10:31.792
Them sons of bitches must have
been doing well over a hundred.

10:31.864 --> 10:34.731
Well, Bob, it's too late
to give them a ticket.

10:34.800 --> 10:38.292
But, if it'll make you
feel any better, you can
shoot their ashes.

10:39.905 --> 10:41.532
What the...

10:42.441 --> 10:43.635
<i>Holy shit!</i>

10:43.709 --> 10:46.906
Hey, mister,
get away from there.

10:46.979 --> 10:50.142
Where the hell you
come from?
This is my car.

10:50.216 --> 10:53.014
Was my car.
Did you see him?

10:53.085 --> 10:55.815
Walking into town,
the guy I was chasing?

10:56.722 --> 10:58.519
Air bags, gotta love 'em.
Did you see him?

11:00.126 --> 11:02.959
- We didn't see anybody.
- Now wait a minute.

11:02.995 --> 11:06.863
Are you telling me
that guy over there
walked out of here too?

11:06.932 --> 11:10.231
Where you goin'? You got
a few questions to answer.

11:11.737 --> 11:14.865
Look, Officers, the man
I'm chasing is dangerous.

11:14.940 --> 11:17.340
<i>If he's in your town,</i>
<i>you got a problem.</i>

11:17.410 --> 11:20.538
We stand here arguing
about a traffic accident...
Do you mind?

11:20.613 --> 11:24.276
<i>Something awful's about</i>
<i>to go down... over there.</i>

11:24.350 --> 11:27.649
Is that where we're going?
It looks like a church.

11:27.720 --> 11:30.450
That's it.
Used to be a church.

11:30.523 --> 11:32.457
Ain't a church no more.

11:32.525 --> 11:35.221
They decommissioned it
in the '50s, due to lack
of interest.

11:42.968 --> 11:45.266
Just the place
I've been looking for.

11:47.406 --> 11:50.204
Gangway, I'm bringing
in business.

11:51.210 --> 11:53.906
What kind of business?

11:53.979 --> 11:56.379
I think he's looking for
a room of his own, Cordelia.

11:56.449 --> 11:58.974
<i>You been drinking,</i>
<i>Uncle Willy?</i>

11:59.051 --> 12:01.986
- I'm clean as a whistle, Irene.
- How long you wanting the room?

12:04.790 --> 12:08.282
I don't know.
One night, maybe two.
Depends.

12:08.360 --> 12:12.319
I never rent short-term,
and I don't rent to strangers.

12:13.766 --> 12:17.497
But I can make exceptions.

12:22.742 --> 12:24.676
<i>[Irene]</i>
<i>Okay.</i>

12:28.848 --> 12:30.941
Enjoy your stay,
Mr.<i>...</i>

12:31.016 --> 12:32.984
Mr. Smith.

12:34.820 --> 12:37.414
Jeryline! Jeryline!

12:37.490 --> 12:40.084
Jeryline, I mean now!

12:40.159 --> 12:42.719
I'm trying
to clean your stove.

12:42.795 --> 12:46.128
How do you expect me
to get my work done
if you keep bothering me?

12:46.198 --> 12:50.498
You've been working so hard
with them clean rubber gloves?

12:50.569 --> 12:52.662
Show Mr. Smith
up to number five.

12:52.738 --> 12:56.538
[Sighing, Muttering]

13:03.282 --> 13:05.341
And then fix him some dinner.

13:05.417 --> 13:08.716
And after that, I got
a few more jobs for you.

13:08.788 --> 13:11.348
<i>This time I'm gonna</i>
<i>watch you.</i>

13:11.423 --> 13:15.359
<i>I want it right</i>
<i>the first time, and that's</i>
<i>all there is to it.</i>

13:15.427 --> 13:17.554
<i>It's my way</i>
<i>or the highway.</i>

13:17.630 --> 13:19.723
Yeah, yeah. Whatever.

13:21.300 --> 13:23.234
[Clears Throat]

13:31.811 --> 13:34.177
What do I need to tell you?

13:34.246 --> 13:37.511
What am I looking at?
Which way is town?

13:37.583 --> 13:41.383
Town is that way,
and you're looking at nothing.

13:41.453 --> 13:45.719
But I'm sure you didn't
come here for a view.
But here's your key.

13:48.127 --> 13:51.995
And the concierge will bring up
your bags momentarily.

13:53.666 --> 13:56.692
<i>[Cordelia]</i>
<i>I don't see how they could</i>
<i>fire you, Wally.</i>

13:56.769 --> 13:58.737
<i>[Wally]</i>
<i>That's what</i>
<i>I told them.</i>

13:58.804 --> 14:01.432
Cordelia, I don't know what
happened to all that mail.

14:01.507 --> 14:04.442
It just disappeared,
but they won't believe me.

14:04.510 --> 14:07.536
God! It's so humiliating.
Do you know what he did?

14:07.613 --> 14:10.605
Uh-uh.
Postmaster comes in...

14:10.683 --> 14:13.083
and he rips my name tag
right off my shirt.

14:13.152 --> 14:15.120
Right in front
of everybody.

14:15.187 --> 14:18.554
And like that's not bad enough,
he took my Mr. Zippy patch.

14:18.624 --> 14:22.025
You should have told your
damn boss to go screw hisself.

14:22.094 --> 14:25.427
Stupid post office.
Ain't the only job in town.

14:25.497 --> 14:27.931
The hell it ain't.
If you had any sense, Wally,

14:28.000 --> 14:30.901
you'd crawl back to him
and beg for the job.

14:30.970 --> 14:34.098
Yeah, well,
I already tried that.

14:34.173 --> 14:36.073
He said no.

14:36.976 --> 14:38.910
Oh, poor Wally.

14:40.479 --> 14:43.573
Where is that girl?
Jeryline!

14:45.751 --> 14:48.914
- What is it?
- Are my sheets done yet?

14:48.988 --> 14:52.890
They're downstairs.
And I couldn't get all those
stains out, either.

14:52.958 --> 14:54.949
Damn guacamole.

14:55.027 --> 14:57.655
Will you put them
on my bed for me?

14:57.730 --> 15:02.429
- Why can't you do it yourself?
You know I'm busy.
- Get her sheets, will you?

15:02.501 --> 15:06.335
No, I just started that stove.
I can't do everything at once.

15:06.405 --> 15:08.737
I'll get them for you,
Cordelia.

15:08.807 --> 15:11.139
Good. Damn.

15:11.210 --> 15:13.576
That's very sweet of you,
Wally.

15:13.646 --> 15:16.843
Put them on your bed?
Thanks.

15:21.754 --> 15:23.654
Oh, poor guy.

15:23.722 --> 15:26.190
Maybe I should give him
a freebie.

15:26.258 --> 15:29.352
Just what he needs,
someone else screwing him.

15:29.662 --> 15:34.099
[Man]
To be perfectly honest, I wasn't
watching the speedometer.

15:34.166 --> 15:37.693
- [Sheriff] Exactly why
were you chasing him?
- He's a thief.

15:37.770 --> 15:42.207
What the hell did he steal
that had you going over
100 miles an hour?

15:45.945 --> 15:47.810
Must have been
pretty valuable.

15:47.880 --> 15:50.371
It is.

15:50.449 --> 15:53.145
<i>[Woman On Radio]</i>
<i>Sheriff?</i>
Yeah, Mavis, go ahead.

15:53.218 --> 15:55.812
<i>We just got a call from Homer</i>
<i>over at the café.</i>

15:55.888 --> 15:58.618
<i>He says somebody tried</i>
<i>to steal his car.</i>

15:59.959 --> 16:01.859
Okay, we're on it.

16:01.927 --> 16:04.691
[Siren Wailing]

16:12.771 --> 16:14.705
<i>[Thunder Rumbling]</i>

16:23.048 --> 16:26.245
- You want some?
- Hell, no.

16:26.318 --> 16:30.345
I was just thinking how much
better that stuff looked
when it was roadkill.

16:30.422 --> 16:32.890
Why don't you shut up?
You eat it.

16:32.958 --> 16:35.483
- She loves me.
- You hurry up and finish and...

16:37.329 --> 16:40.560
I'll take care of dessert.

16:43.235 --> 16:46.693
[Meowing]
Ah, don't worry.

16:46.772 --> 16:49.639
Good Cleo knows better
than to eat that slop.

16:49.708 --> 16:53.337
Goddamn it! Get that
pussy off the table.

16:54.513 --> 16:57.311
I meant the cat.

16:57.383 --> 17:00.784
Cleo!
Didn't I tell you
to put him out?

17:00.853 --> 17:03.549
I did. I don't know
how she got back in.

17:03.622 --> 17:07.079
<i>You finish cleaning</i>
<i>the stove, or you too busy</i>
<i>shooting the breeze?</i>

17:07.159 --> 17:10.321
For Christ's sake, I'll finish
cleaning it tomorrow.

17:10.396 --> 17:12.261
I want it clean tonight.

17:12.330 --> 17:16.893
<i>Remind me of that program</i>
<i>you're on. It's called</i>
<i>"work release", ain't it?</i>

17:16.969 --> 17:20.097
<i>I swear that girl ain't got</i>
<i>no goddamn gratitude.</i>

17:20.172 --> 17:23.107
If I hadn't made a place
for her, she'd be behind bars
or dead.

17:23.175 --> 17:26.008
- Lucky kid.
- Mmm.

17:26.078 --> 17:27.978
<i>[Car Horn Honking]</i>

17:34.553 --> 17:36.714
You expecting somebody,
Mr. Smith?

17:39.658 --> 17:42.320
Evenin', motel people.

17:51.036 --> 17:54.437
<i>[Cordelia] You kept</i>
<i>me waiting, Roach.</i>
<i>Ohh.</i>

17:54.506 --> 17:59.739
<i>I'll tell you the reason I'm late.</i>
<i>Somebody tried to steal Homer's car.</i>

17:59.812 --> 18:02.178
You're kiddin'?
That old hunk of junk?
Yeah.

18:02.247 --> 18:04.272
<i>Right out of the diner</i>
<i>parking lot.</i>

18:04.349 --> 18:08.285
Sheriff and Deputy Dipshit
showed up too.

18:08.353 --> 18:11.845
Damn, you look sweet.
Thank you, honey.

18:14.726 --> 18:17.286
<i>[Roach]</i>
<i>You know, I've been looking</i>
<i>forward to this all week.</i>

18:17.362 --> 18:21.355
That makes two of us.
Hey, what are those
panties you got on there?

18:21.433 --> 18:23.424
I got the cherry flavor.

18:23.502 --> 18:25.129
Are those edible panties?

18:26.872 --> 18:31.070
You know I want pieces
of panty in my salad later.

18:31.143 --> 18:33.976
<i>Oh, Roach,</i>
<i>you're so dirty!</i>

18:37.349 --> 18:39.943
Why don't you set the basket
by the steps, Wally?

18:40.018 --> 18:42.350
She's gonna be needing
clean sheets soon enough.

18:52.564 --> 18:54.930
Your boy did the right thing.
You should be...

18:55.000 --> 18:59.300
That about covers it.
We'll let you know
if we hear anything.

18:59.371 --> 19:01.430
<i>[Mavis On Radio]</i>
<i>Sheriff, you there?</i>

19:03.575 --> 19:05.509
Go ahead, Mavis.

19:05.577 --> 19:09.843
<i>I just got a call from Irene</i>
<i>at the mission about that fellow</i>
<i>you're looking for.</i>

19:09.915 --> 19:13.510
<i>Let's go, Sheriff.</i>
<i>Get in.</i>

19:14.219 --> 19:16.517
<i>[Moaning, Panting]</i>

19:26.865 --> 19:29.800
<i>[Moaning Continues]</i>

19:34.640 --> 19:36.972
He's really holding on tonight,
isn't he?

19:37.042 --> 19:39.010
<i>[Moaning, Screaming]</i>
Okay.

19:39.077 --> 19:41.773
So what were you in for?

19:42.848 --> 19:45.009
I'm not passing judgment.

19:45.083 --> 19:47.711
Stealin'. 'Kay?

19:48.754 --> 19:51.587
<i>[Sirens Wailing]</i>

19:57.829 --> 20:00.957
- Good evening, Irene.
Where is he?
<i>- That's him, in the dining room.</i>

20:01.033 --> 20:06.369
Excuse me, mister. We'd like
to have a word with you about
the fender bender on the highway.

20:06.438 --> 20:10.204
Sheriff, you better
watch it. He's armed.

20:12.144 --> 20:14.078
Told you.

20:14.146 --> 20:17.138
- Drop the guns,
or I'll kill her.
- Don't!

20:17.216 --> 20:20.708
- I said, drop your goddamn guns.
- He won't do it.

20:20.786 --> 20:25.587
- The hell I won't.
- I know this man,
and he will not do it.

20:25.657 --> 20:27.921
<i>Drop the knife.</i>
<i>Drop the goddamn knife!</i>

20:27.993 --> 20:30.052
Her blood's on your head,
asshole.

20:31.597 --> 20:33.565
[Hammers Clicking]

20:33.632 --> 20:35.623
[Clears Throat]

20:43.842 --> 20:45.776
Spread 'em!

20:53.885 --> 20:56.752
<i>Well, well, well.</i>
<i>Mr. Brayker.</i>

20:56.822 --> 21:00.155
- Pleased to make
your acquaintance.
- You lyin' son of a bitch.

21:00.225 --> 21:03.524
<i>[Irene]</i>
<i>Said his name was Smith.</i>

21:03.595 --> 21:05.529
Call it in, Bob.

21:07.432 --> 21:10.367
I believe you'll find what
I'm looking for in there.

21:13.038 --> 21:15.131
What's he got
to do with this?

21:15.207 --> 21:19.541
- I'm... I work
for a collection agency.
- It's empty.

21:19.611 --> 21:22.409
Really.
That can't be.

21:22.481 --> 21:25.541
Well, I guess that means
it's somewhere in the house.

21:27.786 --> 21:31.313
- Keep him away from me!
- Shut up!

21:31.390 --> 21:34.848
Where is it?
I don't know what you're
talking about.

21:34.926 --> 21:38.828
Maybe it's up in his room.
What you guys looking for?

21:38.897 --> 21:42.355
- What the hell are we
looking for anyway?
- A piece of antiquity.

21:42.434 --> 21:45.164
A relic...
in the shape of a key.

21:45.237 --> 21:48.138
- Bob!
- Yeah?

21:48.206 --> 21:51.073
<i>Search his room.</i>
It's number five.

22:02.187 --> 22:05.122
<i>[Man Talking,</i>
<i>Woman Laughing]</i>

22:19.771 --> 22:23.468
<i>[Roach]</i>
<i>Come on, give it to me.</i>
<i>Come on.</i>

22:23.542 --> 22:27.911
<i>Give it to me.</i>
<i>Come on. Ahh!</i>

22:27.979 --> 22:30.072
Come on.
Crank me up.

22:31.650 --> 22:34.778
Come on. Ahh!
God!
Is that good?

22:34.853 --> 22:37.481
- Freeze!
- Ohh!

22:37.556 --> 22:39.524
Jesus Christ, Bob,
you son of a bitch!

22:39.591 --> 22:42.389
<i>Turn it off!</i>
<i>Turn it off!</i>
I'm sorry.

22:42.461 --> 22:44.952
Oh! My nipples are smoking!

22:45.030 --> 22:48.022
Get your clothes on.
Now!

22:48.100 --> 22:51.536
<i>[Sheriff]</i>
<i>Good work, Mavis.</i>
Looky, looky.

22:55.674 --> 22:57.608
<i>I didn't find anything</i>
<i>in the perp's room,</i>

22:57.676 --> 23:00.577
but I sure found something
in the room down the hall.

23:00.612 --> 23:02.512
Thanks, Mavis.

23:04.249 --> 23:07.412
Sorry to drag you down here,
but we'll sort this thing out...

23:07.486 --> 23:09.954
and then you can get back
to your business.

23:10.021 --> 23:13.718
I am assuming it was
personal business, Cordelia.

23:13.792 --> 23:15.726
Actually, Sheriff,

23:15.794 --> 23:18.558
it was kind of like
a tune up and lube job.

23:18.630 --> 23:20.894
Shut up, Bob!
I don't want
to hear about it.

23:20.966 --> 23:23.662
You know how it is when you
get your car...
I don't want to hear it.

23:23.735 --> 23:25.669
Shut up, Bob.

23:25.737 --> 23:28.797
This Brayker fella's
getting more interesting.

23:28.874 --> 23:33.174
<i>According to the computer,</i>
<i>Frank Brayker died over</i>
<i>five years ago.</i>

23:36.748 --> 23:39.376
Who the hell are you?

23:39.451 --> 23:41.385
What's your name?

23:43.221 --> 23:48.022
Maybe if you cool your heels
in a jail cell, you'll be
a little more chatty.

23:48.093 --> 23:51.085
Come on, Bob.
Help me get him to the car.

23:51.163 --> 23:54.621
I'd appreciate getting back
what he stole from me.

23:54.699 --> 23:56.690
<i>That way I can</i>
<i>get on my way,</i>

23:56.768 --> 23:59.965
and you can give this lowlife
what he deserves.

24:00.038 --> 24:02.802
Why don't you tell us
where you put it?

24:02.874 --> 24:06.173
<i>You make it easy for me,</i>
<i>I'll make it easy for you.</i>

24:06.244 --> 24:09.304
- Mind you, you're off
to a pretty bad start.
- I know where it is!

24:09.381 --> 24:13.875
<i>It just occurred to me.</i>
<i>I watched him stash it</i>
<i>and didn't even know it.</i>

24:13.952 --> 24:16.477
Willy, no!
Relax!

24:16.555 --> 24:18.489
I'm sorry, mister.

24:33.438 --> 24:37.636
I'd like you
to put it inside.

24:37.709 --> 24:41.873
<i>[Phone Ringing]</i>
Look what he's done.
He's put somethin' awful inside.

24:41.947 --> 24:45.144
<i>Would you mind dumping that out</i>
<i>before you place it inside?</i>

24:45.217 --> 24:46.844
Sure.

24:46.918 --> 24:49.250
No, don't do it.
He's not what he says he is.

24:49.321 --> 24:51.881
He's just...
Just pop that lid.

24:51.957 --> 24:55.085
I'll take that, Willy.

24:55.160 --> 24:59.324
<i>Bob, escort Mr. Brayker,</i>
<i>or whatever his name is,</i>
<i>out to the car.</i>

24:59.397 --> 25:05.233
Sheriff, I am much obliged
for your assistance
in apprehending...

25:05.303 --> 25:08.704
Don't bother.
You're coming with us.

25:08.773 --> 25:11.640
See, both those cars
were stolen.

25:11.710 --> 25:15.009
We're going down to the station
and we're going to sort
this shit out.

25:15.347 --> 25:18.373
Sheriff, you're making
a big mistake.

25:18.450 --> 25:22.011
It won't be for the first time.
Sorry for the inconvenience.

25:22.087 --> 25:24.885
The man said,
if you knew who I was...

25:24.956 --> 25:27.481
We'll find out soon enough.

25:27.559 --> 25:30.187
[Sighs]
Why wait?

25:30.862 --> 25:33.456
[Screaming]

25:34.466 --> 25:36.434
<i>Give me the keys!</i>

25:38.236 --> 25:40.170
Give me the goddamn keys!

25:46.344 --> 25:48.642
<i>Ah, come on!</i>
<i>Get off me!</i>

25:51.383 --> 25:54.978
Ahhh!

25:55.053 --> 25:57.248
Shit!

26:01.726 --> 26:03.751
Heads up!

26:11.836 --> 26:14.100
Ahhh!

26:18.777 --> 26:23.009
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Humans! You're not worth</i>
<i>the flesh you're printed on!</i>

26:24.683 --> 26:27.049
Fuck this cowboy shit!

26:27.118 --> 26:30.679
You fuckin', hodunk Podunk,
well, then, motherfuckers!

26:32.223 --> 26:34.248
All you had to do was give me
the goddamn key!

26:35.527 --> 26:38.860
<i>Then we could get on</i>
<i>with our lives.</i>

26:38.930 --> 26:41.421
All right, this property...

26:41.499 --> 26:45.230
is hereby... condemned.

27:21.239 --> 27:23.298
<i>Shit!</i>

27:23.375 --> 27:25.400
What is that?

27:28.380 --> 27:30.678
Oh, my God!
Shit!

27:30.749 --> 27:34.810
[Snarling]

27:34.886 --> 27:39.846
[Slurping]

27:39.924 --> 27:42.188
Ahhh!

27:46.197 --> 27:48.859
[Moaning]

27:53.438 --> 27:56.373
[Squealing]

28:17.095 --> 28:19.029
[Screeching]

28:30.341 --> 28:33.276
Oh, great.
What the hell happened
with the lights?

28:34.345 --> 28:36.973
<i>[Thunder Rumbling]</i>
They're gone.

28:38.416 --> 28:40.884
Everybody, back!

28:40.952 --> 28:42.977
Where do you suppose
they went?

28:49.060 --> 28:51.528
What's that smell?

28:51.596 --> 28:53.791
Aaaaah!

28:59.137 --> 29:01.071
Ahhh!

29:15.186 --> 29:17.017
<i>[Roach]</i>
<i>Let's get out of here!</i>

29:22.927 --> 29:24.895
<i>[Irene]</i>
<i>There's more of them!</i>

29:27.866 --> 29:29.959
No, shoot 'em.

29:35.573 --> 29:39.805
<i>Go out the back door.</i>
<i>Come on. Hurry up.</i>
<i>Hurry up.</i>

29:39.878 --> 29:42.278
[Screeching]

29:43.681 --> 29:46.115
[Roaring]
[Screaming]

30:14.979 --> 30:17.573
Oh, that is disgusting.

30:17.649 --> 30:19.583
What the hell is that shit?

30:19.651 --> 30:21.585
Shit!

30:26.324 --> 30:28.315
I don't see them.
Do you see them?
No.

30:28.393 --> 30:31.055
<i>Where the fuck did they go?</i>

30:32.230 --> 30:34.164
Cordelia, stay away
from the door!

30:34.232 --> 30:37.599
You see what I mean?
We can make it to my truck.
No, I don't think so.

30:37.669 --> 30:42.197
Listen! You can stay here
and die if you want to.
I sure as shit ain't.

30:42.273 --> 30:44.741
<i>- [Irene]</i>
<i>Roach, be smart for once.</i>
- Cordelia!

30:48.379 --> 30:51.041
Roach, wait.
Just come on, would ya?

30:51.115 --> 30:54.107
Ahhhh!
[Screaming]

30:59.357 --> 31:02.849
[Shouts]
Cordelia, I'm coming!

31:05.296 --> 31:07.628
I'm sorry.
[Screaming]

31:07.699 --> 31:09.394
Give me that gun!

31:09.467 --> 31:12.129
[Slurping]
Hey, fuck-face!

31:14.606 --> 31:17.632
[Screaming]

31:17.709 --> 31:20.303
Get the eyes!
Get the eyes!

31:26.985 --> 31:30.751
Oh, Wally.
Wally. Oh, God.

31:40.198 --> 31:42.132
Need a hand?
[Gasps]

31:43.368 --> 31:45.495
Give me the key, Brayker.
For cryin' out loud!

31:45.970 --> 31:49.770
Wally? Wally,
please don't die.

31:51.843 --> 31:53.777
Wally?

31:55.713 --> 31:59.342
Oh!
[Panting]

31:59.417 --> 32:02.818
<i>Cordelia!</i>

32:08.059 --> 32:12.655
<i>Brayker, what the hell</i>
<i>are those things?</i>
<i>Demons or something?</i>

32:12.730 --> 32:15.927
Worse.
Demons. That's sweet.
That's just fuckin' sweet!

32:16.000 --> 32:18.833
And they want to kill us
because of you?

32:18.903 --> 32:21.428
Who's going to protect us?
You?

32:21.506 --> 32:25.465
Deputy Bob?
Or the headless horsemen?
We'll be all right.

32:25.543 --> 32:29.843
Just stay inside and stay
together. We just have
to make it through the night.

32:29.914 --> 32:31.973
And that stuff's
gonna keep them out?

32:32.050 --> 32:34.518
There are only two things
we can use against them.

32:34.585 --> 32:36.519
- The blood in this key.
- It's blood?

32:36.587 --> 32:40.990
And anything
that destroys their eyes.
Frees their tortured souls.

32:41.059 --> 32:43.584
- This is crazy!
- Deal with it!

32:43.661 --> 32:47.324
You deal with it.
They got no quarrel with us.

32:47.398 --> 32:51.391
They just want you
and that thing you're carrying.

32:51.469 --> 32:54.836
I say we give it to them.
I say they'll
kill you anyway.

32:54.906 --> 32:58.171
<i>Or possess you. Or use you</i>
<i>to get to the rest of us.</i>

32:58.242 --> 33:00.710
Like it or not,
we stick together.

33:00.778 --> 33:05.078
- My cat's outside.
I gotta get my cat.
- You go out, you stay out.

33:05.149 --> 33:08.516
Is that so?
What are you gonna do?

33:08.586 --> 33:11.680
<i>Shoot us?</i>
Right in the eyes.

33:13.391 --> 33:15.484
Stay down here.

33:15.560 --> 33:17.892
I'm going to seal
the upstairs.

34:42.713 --> 34:44.737
[Gasps]

34:48.853 --> 34:51.286
[Screaming]

34:56.427 --> 34:58.759
- Damn it!
- What are you doing up here?

34:58.830 --> 35:00.798
I thought I told you
to stay downstairs.

35:02.433 --> 35:04.867
Damn!

35:04.936 --> 35:07.302
I thought you might
need help.

35:09.307 --> 35:11.241
[Sighing]

35:14.612 --> 35:18.207
Look, I'm...
I'm sorry about your cat.

35:18.282 --> 35:22.616
And before, with the knife,
I wasn't gonna hurt you.

35:23.588 --> 35:25.522
[Snickering]

35:29.093 --> 35:32.790
I knew you weren't.
I just had a feeling
about you.

35:36.834 --> 35:38.768
Can I ask you something?

35:40.404 --> 35:42.531
Who are you?
Really.

35:45.209 --> 35:47.143
I'm just an old man...

35:48.846 --> 35:51.576
running out of time.

35:57.522 --> 36:00.980
Well, well, well.
Isn't this sweet?

36:01.058 --> 36:04.585
Soiled dove and her
square-jawed postal clerk.

36:04.662 --> 36:08.257
- You're a bastard.
- I ain't the one
who tried to kill you.

36:08.332 --> 36:10.766
Shithead, you left me
out there.

36:10.835 --> 36:13.702
Who in the hell told you
to follow me?

36:14.906 --> 36:17.238
You're absolutely right.
Nobody.

36:17.308 --> 36:19.902
Now I know
who my friends are.

36:23.414 --> 36:25.882
Whores ain't got no friends.

36:27.985 --> 36:29.919
<i>[Brayker]</i>
<i>That's all the doors</i>
<i>and window sealed.</i>

36:29.987 --> 36:34.720
Any other ways in or out
of this place?
Aside from doors and windows?

36:35.927 --> 36:38.862
Got some place you
want us to put him?

36:54.779 --> 36:57.805
Jeryline, let's go
make some coffee.

36:57.882 --> 37:00.282
Looks like we're in
for a long night.

37:06.490 --> 37:09.891
Where did you
get that from?
It was my husband's.

37:09.961 --> 37:13.328
[Meowing]
Cleo! Hi, baby.

37:13.397 --> 37:17.231
You let the cat in.
She just appeared.

37:17.301 --> 37:19.235
Brayker, what are you doing?

37:19.303 --> 37:21.794
Animals aren't immune.
They can be possessed.

37:21.872 --> 37:24.841
- [Hissing]
- Give me the cat! Shit!

37:27.245 --> 37:29.270
<i>What the hell's going on?</i>
The cat. The cat.

37:29.347 --> 37:34.444
Brayker, my cat is not possessed
by some demon from hell.

37:35.686 --> 37:37.586
We'll see.

37:37.655 --> 37:39.589
Listen, I got
to talk to you.
What?

37:39.657 --> 37:42.854
I got nothing to say.
I just gotta talk to you
for a second.

37:42.927 --> 37:46.693
I don't want to talk. Why don't
you bother somebody else?
Just for a second.

37:46.764 --> 37:49.927
You want to talk?
Let's talk about how you
abandoned Cordelia.

37:50.001 --> 37:52.902
How you left her to die.
Huh?

37:52.970 --> 37:56.269
I hope you're ashamed
of yourself.
Not particularly, no.

37:56.340 --> 37:59.639
Everybody's got
to look out their selves.

37:59.710 --> 38:03.771
- I'm for getting out of here.
- No one's going anywhere
till Mr. Brayker says so.

38:03.848 --> 38:06.339
Hey, fuck him!
This is his fight.

38:06.417 --> 38:09.545
<i>[Roach]</i>
<i>You may want to die in</i>
<i>this motel, but I don't.</i>

38:09.620 --> 38:14.580
I want to get that key,
and I want to give it
to those things out there.

38:14.659 --> 38:17.856
Hey, Roach.
Haven't you caused
just about enough trouble?

38:17.928 --> 38:21.830
Excuse me. I'm trying
to have a conversation
with my friend, Wally.

38:21.899 --> 38:25.733
He's not your friend.
Assholes don't have friends.

38:28.739 --> 38:30.673
Excuse us.

38:30.741 --> 38:33.437
Can I talk to you
for a second, please?

38:37.948 --> 38:40.781
Jesus, Roach!

38:40.851 --> 38:44.912
So... you got yourself
a new boyfriend.

38:44.989 --> 38:46.923
You get in my way
and I'll kill you.

38:46.991 --> 38:49.585
Keep it in your pants
for a change.

38:49.660 --> 38:51.685
I'm warning you, bitch.

38:51.762 --> 38:54.731
I'm not afraid of you.
No?

38:54.799 --> 38:57.734
[Yells]

38:57.802 --> 39:00.032
You better be afraid
of me.

39:10.414 --> 39:13.178
<i>Come here, girl.</i>
<i>Come on.</i>

39:14.952 --> 39:16.886
<i>Cleo, come on.</i>

39:21.525 --> 39:24.961
Cleo?
Come to mommy.

39:25.029 --> 39:27.759
<i>Come on.</i>
<i>Come here, girl.</i>

39:27.832 --> 39:31.324
Come here, Cleo.
Come on.

39:31.402 --> 39:33.700
- [Cat Hissing]
- [Gasping]

39:35.272 --> 39:38.730
<i>I got you, girl.</i>
<i>Come on, Brayker.</i>

39:40.444 --> 39:44.813
See, I told you.
Hey, look...
where she came from.

39:44.882 --> 39:46.816
<i>[Wind Blowing]</i>

39:50.454 --> 39:52.388
Breeze.

39:55.459 --> 39:57.393
[Sobbing]

40:09.340 --> 40:11.240
[Gasps]

40:16.580 --> 40:18.514
<i>[Thunder Rumbling]</i>

40:24.021 --> 40:27.388
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Poor, Cordelia.</i>

40:27.458 --> 40:32.555
<i>Seems downright criminal</i>
<i>to treat a pretty girl</i>
<i>that way.</i>

40:32.630 --> 40:36.088
<i>Did I say pretty?</i>
<i>I meant beautiful.</i>

40:36.167 --> 40:40.297
<i>'Cause you are.</i>
<i>You are beautiful,</i>
<i>Cordelia.</i>

40:40.371 --> 40:43.033
<i>Inside and out.</i>

40:43.107 --> 40:46.270
<i>Maybe nobody here</i>
<i>can see it,</i>
<i>but I sure can.</i>

40:47.645 --> 40:50.045
<i>I understand you.</i>

40:50.114 --> 40:52.378
<i>I know what you want.</i>

40:52.450 --> 40:55.317
<i>I know what you need.</i>

40:55.386 --> 40:57.718
<i>Guys like Roach,</i>
<i>they think...</i>

40:57.788 --> 41:01.155
<i>just because they're paying</i>
<i>for it that they can</i>
<i>treat you like shit.</i>

41:01.225 --> 41:03.955
[Thinking]
If they spend the same money
on dinner and a movie,

41:04.028 --> 41:07.259
they can call you "girlfriend"
instead of "whore."

41:07.331 --> 41:10.061
<i>Whore, what a horrible word</i>
<i>that is...</i>

41:10.134 --> 41:14.537
to use on someone
who's really just a sad girl
who's looking for love.

41:17.341 --> 41:20.868
<i>Tender, warm,</i>
<i>unconditional love.</i>

41:22.213 --> 41:26.547
I can give you that love,
as much as you can take.

41:40.431 --> 41:44.925
All you have to do
is let me in.

41:45.002 --> 41:47.436
<i>Let me in.</i>

41:47.505 --> 41:50.531
<i>Let me in.</i>

41:50.608 --> 41:52.974
<i>Let me in.</i>

41:53.043 --> 41:55.773
<i>Let me in.</i>

41:56.747 --> 41:59.181
Cordelia?

42:03.854 --> 42:05.822
<i>Cordelia?</i>

42:07.291 --> 42:09.521
Cordelia?
You okay?

42:11.262 --> 42:13.856
- Hello, Wally.
- Hello, Cordelia.

42:17.101 --> 42:21.367
I realized something awful
about myself tonight, Wally.

42:21.438 --> 42:24.930
My whole life, I've avoided
the guys who really loved me.

42:26.944 --> 42:28.605
Like you.

42:32.483 --> 42:35.611
You really love me,
don't you, Wally?

42:35.686 --> 42:39.486
Yes, Cordelia,
I really love you.

42:41.292 --> 42:44.159
I've always loved you.

42:44.228 --> 42:47.561
From the very first time
I delivered your mail.

42:49.767 --> 42:52.702
Well, don't just do it
with your eyes, Wally.

43:00.711 --> 43:02.906
It's some kind of tunnel.
It's a mine shaft.

43:02.980 --> 43:06.916
Not surprising.
The whole area's
riddled with them.

43:06.984 --> 43:09.111
This means this
is a way out.

43:09.186 --> 43:13.555
We can get to town
before those things
find out we're gone.

43:13.624 --> 43:16.559
No.

43:16.627 --> 43:19.391
No, it's too risky.

43:19.463 --> 43:21.988
What?
Now, listen. What
the hell are you saying?

43:22.066 --> 43:24.591
Trust me.
You're safer in this house.

43:24.668 --> 43:27.296
<i>[Screaming]</i>

43:27.371 --> 43:30.499
- Shit!
<i>- [Screaming Continues]</i>

43:30.574 --> 43:32.508
What was that?

43:34.244 --> 43:37.042
<i>- [Screaming]</i>
- What's going on?

43:38.515 --> 43:41.006
- Oh, God!
<i>- [Jeryline]</i>
<i>What's in there?</i>

43:41.085 --> 43:43.553
<i>[Screaming Continues]</i>

43:43.621 --> 43:46.647
- Cordelia?
- Ahhhh!

43:54.131 --> 43:56.065
Oh, man!

43:58.902 --> 44:02.736
<i>- [Roach]</i>
<i>Shoot it, damn it!</i>
- I can't! I can't!

44:02.806 --> 44:04.740
Shoot 'em both!

44:11.081 --> 44:13.549
[Roaring]

44:19.657 --> 44:21.625
Stop it, stop it!

44:28.098 --> 44:30.089
Ahhh!

44:32.436 --> 44:34.336
Irene!

44:35.239 --> 44:37.230
Ahhhh!

44:43.681 --> 44:45.546
Ahhhh!

44:49.319 --> 44:52.254
Ohh!

44:55.259 --> 44:57.193
Go ahead.
[Moaning]

44:59.263 --> 45:02.255
[Screaming]
Give it to me!

45:02.332 --> 45:05.529
Shit!
It's still bleeding.
Here.

45:05.602 --> 45:10.130
We've got to get her outta here.
She'll bleed to death.

45:10.207 --> 45:12.437
We've got to take
our chances in the mines.

45:12.509 --> 45:16.809
The spur that runs under here
comes to a head in a mile.

45:16.880 --> 45:19.644
- I say we do it.
- Fuck, yeah.

45:19.717 --> 45:22.151
What makes you think
they haven't found the mines?

45:22.219 --> 45:26.553
<i>Has everybody fuckin' had it</i>
<i>with you tellin' us what to do?</i>

45:26.623 --> 45:29.148
<i>If we want to go out to the</i>
<i>mines, we're going out that way.</i>

45:29.226 --> 45:31.217
We don't need
your fuckin' permission.

45:31.295 --> 45:34.093
<i>I got an idea that's gonna</i>
<i>save us that walk.</i>

